value.value: Adult neuron that has postsynaptic sites in the ipsilateral wedge and lateral accessory lobe and presynaptic sites in the contralateral lateral accessory lobe (Franconville et al., 2018). It has presynapses in the contralateral lateral accessory lobe (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 2 of these cells per organism (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024).

definition.value: Uncharacterized putative cell type based on Hemibrain data (Scheffer et al., 2020) and updated using FlyWire (FAFB) data (Dorkenwald et al., 2024). Soma locations are based on the closest annotated neuropil region. Pre- or post-synapse locations are the fewest regions that collectively contain at least 80 percent of all pre- or post-synapses of these neurons in FlyWire. Neurotransmitter predictions are from Eckstein et al. (2024). Other annotations are based on annotations in FlyWire and are available in the supplemental material of Schlegel et al. (2024).

value.value: Adult neuron belonging to group 163 of the terra incognita neurons with substantial synapsing in the lateral accessory lobe (Scheffer et al., 2020). It has postsynaptic sites in the lateral accessory lobe, lateral complex, ventromedial neuropils, inferior neuropils, epaulette, vest and crepine (Scheffer et al., 2020). It has presynaptic sites in the lateral accessory lobe, lateral complex, ventromedial neuropils, inferior neuropils, epaulette, vest and crepine (Scheffer et al., 2020).

definition.value: Uncharacterized putative cell type (based on clustering analysis) from Janelia hemibrain data (Scheffer et al., 2020). Connectivity based on Hemibrain v1.1 data where each individual of this type has at least 10 synapses in a region.
